import keras
import numpy as np
from keras.layers import Dense
from keras.models import Sequential
import pandas as pd
from keras.utils import np_utils
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
from sklearn.model_selection import KFold
from tensorflow.python.keras.optimizer_v1 import sgd

m_train = pd.read_csv('mnist_train.csv')
m_test = pd.read_csv('mnist_test.csv')

x_train = m_train.drop('label', axis=1)
y_train = m_train['label']
x_test = m_test.drop('label', axis=1)
y_test = m_test['label']

image_size = 784  # 28*28
n = 10



# one-hot encoding

y_train = np_utils.to_categorical(y_train, n)
y_test = np_utils.to_categorical(y_test, n)
x_train = x_train.to_numpy()
x_test = x_test.to_numpy()

# normalization

x_test = x_test / 255
x_train = x_train / 255

# NN
def define_model():
    model = Sequential()

    # The input layer requires the special input_shape parameter which should match
    # the shape of our training data.
    model.add(Dense(units=32, activation='sigmoid', input_shape=(image_size,)))
    model.add(Dense(units=n, activation='softmax'))
    model.summary()

    opt = keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001)
    model.compile(optimizer=opt, loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model


print(np.shape(x_train))
print(x_train)
print(np.shape(y_train))
print(y_train)

kfold = KFold(5, shuffle=True, random_state=1)
histories, accuracies, losses = list(), list(), list()
train_ix = 0
test_ix = 0
for train_ix, test_ix in kfold.split(x_train, y_train):
    model = define_model()
   # trainX, trainY, testX, testY = x_train[train_ix], y_train[train_ix], x_test[test_ix], y_test[test_ix]
    history = model.fit(x_train[train_ix], y_train[train_ix], batch_size=32, epochs=10, verbose=0, validation_data=(x_test[test_ix], y_test[test_ix]))
    loss, accuracy = model.evaluate(x_test[test_ix], y_test[test_ix], verbose=0)
    print('> %.3f' % (accuracy * 100.0))
    accuracies.append(accuracy)
    histories.append(history)
    losses.append(loss)
